Ivory Coast were held to a 0-0 draw by Togo as they began the defence of their African Nations Cup title with an uninspiring display in the opening Group C game on Monday.It was the fourth draw in the opening five games at this year&#8217;s finals where none of the pre-tournament favourites have made an impact but will be a seen as a moral victory for Togo.The Togolese are the outsiders in the group but looked the sharper of the two teams in attack although the game delivered just a handful of half chances.The Democratic Republic of Congo and Morocco meet later on Monday in Oyem in the second Group C encounter.-Reuters